5: Hey, Jester. Same chores as always?
9:
You got it. I'll be tinkering with my
traps in the usual place. If you need
anything, just holler.
13:
You sure spend a lot of time on those
traps.
15:
Maybe if you spent half that time
ranching, you wouldn't have needed
to hire extra help.
21:
Tsk tsk. Oh Alk, how could you be so
blind? Don't you see—without the
traps, the cattle are vulnerable to all
sorts of danger! I am only doing
my job!
24:
Plus, with you two around, this ranch
has been running as smooth as butter
on a bald monkey.
27:
Light looks after the cattle, you do the
cleaning and carving, and I design the
snares!
30:
Heh-heh-heh. You couldn't find a
more efficient party, not if you crawled
all the dungeons in the world!
41:
All right! Now enough jaw-flapping!
I think we'll take a little detour into the
forest before work today. Got a trap
there that needs maintaining.
46: Heeey! Let me down from here!
49:
Well, look at that. One fool of a
criminal, trussed up like a
Thanksgiving turkey.
52: Oof... I feel kind of bad for him.
57:
I thought these traps were for
monsters.
60:
Well, truth is, I've got another contract
going with the Guild.
62:
Lots of criminals try to escape into
these woods, after blowing it in
Palpebra. And most of them get
caught in my traps.
64:
When I told the Guild, they looked
about ready to break out in a jig.
Showered me with money. Since then,
we've had this give-and-take
relationship.
66:
I give them the wrongdoers, and take
the bounty. It's how I've been funding
my snare enterprise, by the way.
70:
Well, that explains why you prefer
trap-making to cow-sitting.
74:
Heh. Oh yes, the money's good. But
the mental exercise—that's the real
prize. Designing those snares makes
me feel alive!
77: Cool. So, we heading to the Guild now?
90:
Oh. Well, there's no rush there,
gentlemen.
93:
It ain't every day you snag such
a lively specimen. Got a few traps
I'd like to try out on him.
99:
No! What if he gets hurt? Save it for
the monsters!
103:
Come on, Alk. This fine man has
broken the law! Surely we don't need
to feel bad for giving him a few
scrapes and bruises.
108:
*sigh* Whatever. I'm going to the
Guild, Jester, whether you like it or not!
114:
I wouldn't go wandering alone in these
woods if I were you. Not unless you're
itching to be snapped up by my
snares.
118:
Gee... Sure would've been nice if you
told us BEFORE leading us into the jaws
of death.
125:
Oh yeah. Wanted to take precautions.
Had a few rats that managed to
scrabble their way out of a previous
design.
128:
Could innocent people get trapped
down there?
132:
...Mm... Perhaps. I never gave it much
thought. Hey, Alk. Think you could
lower yourself in there and make sure
it's empty?
138: Why don't you do it YOURSELF?!
